{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"When most people think about the beginnings"},{"time":2000,"text":"of AIDS, they're gonna think back to the 1980s."},{"time":5000,"text":"And certainly, this was the decade in which we discovered AIDS"},{"time":8000,"text":"and the virus that causes it, HIV."},{"time":11000,"text":"But in fact this virus crossed over into humans many decades before,"},{"time":15000,"text":"from chimpanzees, where the virus originated, into humans who hunt these apes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":19000,"text":"This photo was taken before the Great Depression"},{"time":22000,"text":"in Brazzaville, Congo."},{"time":24000,"text":"At this time, there were thousands of individuals,"},{"time":26000,"text":"we think, that were infected with HIV."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28000,"text":"So I have a couple of really important questions for you."},{"time":30000,"text":"If this virus was in thousands"},{"time":31000,"text":"of individuals at this point,"},{"time":33000,"text":"why was it the case that it took us until 1984"},{"time":36000,"text":"to be able to discover this virus?"},{"time":38000,"text":"OK now, more importantly,"},{"time":40000,"text":"had we been there in the '40s and '50s, '60s,"},{"time":43000,"text":"had we seen this disease, had we understood"},{"time":46000,"text":"exactly what was going on with it, how might that have changed and completely"},{"time":49000,"text":"transformed the nature of the way this pandemic moved?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":54000,"text":"In fact, this is not unique to HIV. The vast majority of"},{"time":57000,"text":"viruses come from animals."},{"time":59000,"text":"And you can kind of think of this as a pyramid of this bubbling up of viruses"},{"time":62000,"text":"from animals into human populations."},{"time":64000,"text":"But only at the very top of this pyramid do these things become completely human."},{"time":67000,"text":"Nevertheless, we spend the vast majority"},{"time":70000,"text":"of our energy focused on this level of the pyramid,"},{"time":72000,"text":"trying to tackle things that are already completely adapted to human beings,"},{"time":76000,"text":"that are going to be very very difficult to address --"},{"time":78000,"text":"as we've seen in the case of HIV."}]},{"cues":[{"time":80000,"text":"So during the last 15 years,"},{"time":82000,"text":"I've been working to actually study the earlier interface here --"},{"time":85000,"text":"what I've labeled \"viral chatter,\" which was a term coined"},{"time":87000,"text":"by my mentor Don Burke."},{"time":89000,"text":"This is the idea that we can study the sort of"},{"time":91000,"text":"pinging of these viruses into human populations,"},{"time":94000,"text":"the movement of these agents over into humans;"},{"time":96000,"text":"and by capturing this moment,"},{"time":98000,"text":"we might be able to move to a situation where we can catch them early."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101000,"text":"OK, so this is a picture, and I'm going to show you"},{"time":103000,"text":"some pictures now from the field."},{"time":105000,"text":"This is a picture of a central African hunter."},{"time":107000,"text":"It's actually a fairly common picture."},{"time":109000,"text":"One of the things I want you to note from it"},{"time":111000,"text":"is blood -- that you see a tremendous amount of blood contact."},{"time":114000,"text":"This was absolutely key for us. This is a"},{"time":116000,"text":"very intimate form of connection."},{"time":118000,"text":"So if we're going to study viral chatter, we need to"},{"time":120000,"text":"get to these populations who have intensive contact with wild animals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123000,"text":"And so we've been studying people like this individual."},{"time":127000,"text":"We collect blood from them, other specimens."},{"time":130000,"text":"We look at the diseases, which are in the animals as well as the humans."},{"time":133000,"text":"And ideally, this is going to allow us to catch these things"},{"time":136000,"text":"early on, as they're moving over into human populations."},{"time":139000,"text":"And the basic objective of this work is not to just"},{"time":141000,"text":"go out once and look at these individuals,"},{"time":143000,"text":"but to establish thousands of individuals"},{"time":145000,"text":"in these populations that we would monitor"},{"time":148000,"text":"continuously on a regular basis."},{"time":150000,"text":"When they were sick, we would collect specimens from them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152000,"text":"We would actually enlist them --"},{"time":154000,"text":"which we've done now -- to collect specimens from animals."},{"time":156000,"text":"We give them these little pieces of filter paper."},{"time":158000,"text":"When they sample from animals,"},{"time":160000,"text":"they collect the blood on the filter paper"},{"time":162000,"text":"and this allows us to identify yet-unknown viruses from exactly the right animals --"},{"time":166000,"text":"the ones that are actually being hunted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":172000,"text":"(Video) Narrator: Deep in a remote region of Cameroon,"},{"time":174000,"text":"two hunters stalk their prey."},{"time":177000,"text":"Their names are Patrice and Patee."},{"time":179000,"text":"They're searching for bush meat;"},{"time":182000,"text":"forest animals they can kill to feed their families."},{"time":186000,"text":"Patrice and Patee set out most days to go out hunting"},{"time":188000,"text":"in the forest around their homes."},{"time":191000,"text":"They have a series of traps, of snares that they've set up"},{"time":193000,"text":"to catch wild pigs, snakes, monkeys,"},{"time":197000,"text":"rodents -- anything they can, really."},{"time":201000,"text":"Patrice and Patee have been out for hours but found nothing."},{"time":207000,"text":"The animals are simply gone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":211000,"text":"We stop for a drink of water."},{"time":216000,"text":"Then there is a rustle in the brush."},{"time":221000,"text":"A group of hunters approach,"},{"time":226000,"text":"their packs loaded with wild game."},{"time":230000,"text":"There's at least three viruses"},{"time":232000,"text":"that you know about, which are in this particular monkey."}]},{"cues":[{"time":235000,"text":"Nathan Wolfe: This species, yeah. And there's many many more pathogens"},{"time":237000,"text":"that are present in these animals."},{"time":239000,"text":"These individuals are at specific risk,"},{"time":242000,"text":"particularly if there's blood contact, they're at risk for transmission"},{"time":245000,"text":"and possibly infection with novel viruses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250000,"text":"Narrator: As the hunters display their kills, something surprising happens."},{"time":253000,"text":"They show us filter paper they've used to collect the animals' blood."},{"time":257000,"text":"The blood will be tested for zoonotic viruses,"},{"time":260000,"text":"part of a program Dr. Wolfe has spent years setting up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":263000,"text":"NW: So this is from this animal right here,"},{"time":265000,"text":"Greater Spot-Nosed Guenon."},{"time":267000,"text":"Every person who has one of those filter papers has at least,"},{"time":269000,"text":"at a minimum, been through our basic health education"},{"time":272000,"text":"about the risks associated with these activities,"},{"time":275000,"text":"which presumably, from our perspective,"},{"time":277000,"text":"gives them the ability to decrease their own risk,"},{"time":279000,"text":"and then obviously the risk to their families,"},{"time":282000,"text":"the village, the country, and the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":286000,"text":"NW: OK, before I continue, I think it's important to take just a moment"},{"time":289000,"text":"to talk about bush meat. Bush meat is the hunting of wild game."},{"time":292000,"text":"OK? And you can consider all sorts of different bush meat."},{"time":294000,"text":"I'm going to be talking about this."},{"time":296000,"text":"When your children and grandchildren"},{"time":298000,"text":"sort of pose questions to you about this period of time,"},{"time":300000,"text":"one of the things they're gonna ask you,"},{"time":302000,"text":"is how it was they we allowed some of our closest living relatives,"},{"time":305000,"text":"some of the most valuable and endangered species"},{"time":307000,"text":"on our planet, to go extinct because we"},{"time":310000,"text":"weren't able to address some of the issues"},{"time":312000,"text":"of poverty in these parts of the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314000,"text":"But in fact that's not the only question they're going to ask you about this."},{"time":317000,"text":"They're also going to ask you the question"},{"time":319000,"text":"that when we knew that this was the way that HIV entered"},{"time":321000,"text":"into the human population,"},{"time":323000,"text":"and that other diseases had the potential to enter like this,"},{"time":325000,"text":"why did we let these behaviors continue?"},{"time":327000,"text":"Why did we not find some other solution to this?"},{"time":329000,"text":"They're going to say, in regions of profound"},{"time":332000,"text":"instability throughout the world,"},{"time":334000,"text":"where you have intense poverty, where populations are growing"},{"time":337000,"text":"and you don't have sustainable resources like this,"},{"time":339000,"text":"this is going to lead to food insecurity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344000,"text":"But they're also going to ask you probably a different question."},{"time":346000,"text":"It's one that I think we all need to ask ourselves,"},{"time":348000,"text":"which is, why we thought the responsibility rested with this individual here."},{"time":352000,"text":"Now this is the individual -- you can see just right up over his right shoulder --"},{"time":355000,"text":"this is the individual that hunted the monkey"},{"time":357000,"text":"from the last picture that I showed you."},{"time":359000,"text":"OK, take a look at his shirt."},{"time":361000,"text":"You know, take a look at his face."},{"time":364000,"text":"Bush meat is one of the central crises,"},{"time":367000,"text":"which is occurring in our population right now,"},{"time":369000,"text":"in humanity, on this planet."},{"time":371000,"text":"But it can't be the fault of somebody like this."},{"time":374000,"text":"OK? And solving it cannot be his responsibility alone."},{"time":378000,"text":"There's no easy solutions,"},{"time":380000,"text":"but what I'm saying to you is that we neglect this problem"},{"time":382000,"text":"at our own peril."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384000,"text":"So, in 1998, along with my mentors"},{"time":387000,"text":"Don Burke and Colonel Mpoudi-Ngole,"},{"time":389000,"text":"we went to actually start this work"},{"time":391000,"text":"in Central Africa, to work with hunters"},{"time":393000,"text":"in this part of the world."},{"time":395000,"text":"And my job -- at that time I was a post-doctoral fellow,"},{"time":398000,"text":"and I was really tasked with setting this up."},{"time":400000,"text":"So I said to myself, \"OK, great --"},{"time":402000,"text":"we're gonna collect all kinds of specimens. We're gonna go to all these"},{"time":404000,"text":"different locations. It's going to be wonderful.\""},{"time":407000,"text":"You know, I looked at the map; I picked out 17 sites;"},{"time":409000,"text":"I figured, no problem."},{"time":411000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":413000,"text":"Needless to say, I was drastically wrong."},{"time":415000,"text":"This is challenging work to do."},{"time":417000,"text":"Fortunately, I had and continue to have"},{"time":419000,"text":"an absolutely wonderful team of colleagues and collaborators in my own team,"},{"time":422000,"text":"and that's the only way that this work can really occur."},{"time":424000,"text":"We have a whole range of challenges about this work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":427000,"text":"One of them is just obtaining trust"},{"time":429000,"text":"from individuals that we work with in the field."},{"time":431000,"text":"The person you see on the right hand side is Paul DeLong-Minutu."},{"time":435000,"text":"He's one of the best communicators that I've really ever dealt with."},{"time":437000,"text":"When I arrived I didn't speak a word of French,"},{"time":439000,"text":"and I still seemed to understand what it was he was saying."},{"time":442000,"text":"Paul worked for years"},{"time":444000,"text":"on the Cameroonian national radio and television,"},{"time":446000,"text":"and he spoke about health issues. He was a health correspondent."},{"time":449000,"text":"So we figured we'd hire this person -- when we got there he could"},{"time":451000,"text":"be a great communicator."},{"time":453000,"text":"When we would get to these rural villages, though, what we found out"},{"time":455000,"text":"is that no one had television,"},{"time":457000,"text":"so they wouldn't recognize his face."},{"time":460000,"text":"But -- when he began to speak"},{"time":463000,"text":"they would actually recognize his voice from the radio."},{"time":465000,"text":"And this was somebody who had incredible"},{"time":467000,"text":"potential to spread aspects of our message,"},{"time":469000,"text":"whether it be with regards to wildlife conservation"},{"time":472000,"text":"or health prevention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":475000,"text":"Often we run into obstacles. This is us coming back from"},{"time":477000,"text":"one of these very rural sites,"},{"time":479000,"text":"with specimens from 200 individuals"},{"time":481000,"text":"that we needed to get back to the lab within 48 hours."},{"time":483000,"text":"I like to show this shot -- this is"},{"time":485000,"text":"Ubald Tamoufe, who's the lead"},{"time":487000,"text":"investigator in our Cameroon site."},{"time":489000,"text":"Ubald laughs at me when I show this photo"},{"time":491000,"text":"because of course you can't see his face."},{"time":493000,"text":"But the reason I like to show the shot"},{"time":495000,"text":"is because you can see that he's about to solve this problem."},{"time":498000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":499000,"text":"Which -- which he did, which he did."},{"time":502000,"text":"Just a few quick before and after shots."},{"time":504000,"text":"This was our laboratory before."},{"time":507000,"text":"This is what it looks like now."},{"time":509000,"text":"Early on, in order to ship our specimens,"},{"time":511000,"text":"we had to have dry ice. To get dry ice we had to go"},{"time":513000,"text":"to the breweries -- beg, borrow, steal to get these folks to give it to us."},{"time":516000,"text":"Now we have our own liquid nitrogen."},{"time":519000,"text":"I like to call our laboratory the coldest place in Central Africa -- it might be."},{"time":524000,"text":"And here's a shot of me, this is the before shot of me."},{"time":528000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":530000,"text":"No comment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":532000,"text":"So what happened? So during the 10 years that we've been doing"},{"time":534000,"text":"this work, we actually surprised ourselves."},{"time":537000,"text":"We made a number of discoveries."},{"time":540000,"text":"And what we've found is that if you look in the right place,"},{"time":542000,"text":"you can actually monitor the flow"},{"time":544000,"text":"of these viruses into human populations."},{"time":546000,"text":"That gave us a tremendous amount of hope."},{"time":548000,"text":"What we've found is a whole range of new viruses in these individuals,"},{"time":551000,"text":"including new viruses in the same group"},{"time":553000,"text":"as HIV -- so, brand new retroviruses."},{"time":556000,"text":"And let's face it, any new retrovirus in the"},{"time":558000,"text":"human population -- it's something we should be aware of."},{"time":561000,"text":"It's something we should be following. It's not something"},{"time":563000,"text":"that we should be surprised by."}]},{"cues":[{"time":565000,"text":"Needless to say in the past"},{"time":567000,"text":"these viruses entering into these rural communities"},{"time":569000,"text":"might very well have gone extinct."},{"time":571000,"text":"That's no longer the case. Logging roads provide access to urban areas."},{"time":575000,"text":"And critically, what happens in central Africa"},{"time":579000,"text":"doesn't stay in Central Africa."},{"time":582000,"text":"So, once we discovered that it was really possible"},{"time":584000,"text":"that we could actually do this monitoring,"},{"time":586000,"text":"we decided to move this from research, to"},{"time":588000,"text":"really attempt to phase up to a global monitoring effort."},{"time":592000,"text":"Through generous support and partnership"},{"time":594000,"text":"scientifically with Google.org and the Skoll Foundation,"},{"time":597000,"text":"we were able to start the Global Viral Forecasting Initiative"},{"time":601000,"text":"and begin work in four different sites"},{"time":603000,"text":"in Africa and Asia."},{"time":606000,"text":"Needless to say, different populations from different parts of the world"},{"time":608000,"text":"have different sorts of contact."},{"time":610000,"text":"So it's not just hunters in Central Africa."},{"time":613000,"text":"It's also working in live animal markets --"},{"time":615000,"text":"these wet markets -- which is exactly the place where"},{"time":617000,"text":"SARS emerged in Asia."},{"time":619000,"text":"But really, this is just the beginning from our perspective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":621000,"text":"Our objective right now, in addition to"},{"time":623000,"text":"deploying to these sites and getting everything moving,"},{"time":625000,"text":"is to identify new partners"},{"time":627000,"text":"because we feel like this effort needs to be extended"},{"time":630000,"text":"to probably 20 or more sites throughout the world -- to viral hotspots --"},{"time":634000,"text":"because really the idea here is to cast an incredibly wide net"},{"time":637000,"text":"so that we can catch these things, ideally,"},{"time":639000,"text":"before they make it to blood banks,"},{"time":641000,"text":"sexual networks, airplanes. And that's really our objective."},{"time":645000,"text":"There was a time not very long ago"},{"time":647000,"text":"when the discovery of unknown organisms"},{"time":649000,"text":"was something that held incredible awe for us."},{"time":652000,"text":"It had potential to really change the way that we saw ourselves,"},{"time":655000,"text":"and thought about ourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":657000,"text":"Many people, I think, on our planet right now"},{"time":659000,"text":"despair, and they think"},{"time":662000,"text":"we've reached a point where we've discovered most of the things."},{"time":665000,"text":"I'm going tell you right now: please don't despair."},{"time":668000,"text":"If an intelligent extra-terrestrial"},{"time":670000,"text":"was taxed with writing the encyclopedia of life on our planet,"},{"time":673000,"text":"27 out of 30 of these volumes"},{"time":675000,"text":"would be devoted to bacteria and virus,"},{"time":678000,"text":"with just a few of the volumes left"},{"time":680000,"text":"for plants, fungus and animals,"},{"time":682000,"text":"humans being a footnote;"},{"time":685000,"text":"interesting footnote but a footnote nonetheless."},{"time":688000,"text":"This is honestly the most exciting period"},{"time":691000,"text":"ever for the study of unknown life forms on our planet."},{"time":695000,"text":"The dominant things that exist here"},{"time":697000,"text":"we know almost nothing about."},{"time":699000,"text":"And yet finally, we have the tools, which will allow us to actually explore that world"},{"time":702000,"text":"and understand them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":706000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":708000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}